					<item>
		<title><![CDATA[ACE THE INTERVIEW]]></title>
		<link>https://cisbridge.commons.gc.cuny.edu/2025/09/30/ace-the-interview/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 30 Sep 2025 23:39:47 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[suraiyapm]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://cisbridge.commons.gc.cuny.edu/?p=185</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<!-- wp:gallery {"linkTo":"none"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped"><!-- wp:image {"id":187,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/files.commons.gc.cuny.edu/wp-content/blogs.dir/43977/files/2025/09/1-791x1024.png?amp;X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&amp;X-Amz-Credential=AKIAZUO33UBRWHMWHNJB/20250930/us-east-1/s3/aws4_request&amp;X-Amz-Date=20250930T233239Z&amp;X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host&amp;X-Amz-Expires=21600&amp;X-Amz-Signature=262ce861604bb30a397293350313d807842634174221c99240ca3004172b3d4b" alt="Ace the Interview Workshop event flyer front page." class="wp-image-187" /></figure>
<!-- /wp:image --></figure>
<!-- /wp:gallery -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":191,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/files.commons.gc.cuny.edu/wp-content/blogs.dir/43977/files/2025/09/2-1-791x1024.png?amp;X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&amp;X-Amz-Credential=AKIAZUO33UBRWHMWHNJB/20250930/us-east-1/s3/aws4_request&amp;X-Amz-Date=20250930T233240Z&amp;X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host&amp;X-Amz-Expires=21600&amp;X-Amz-Signature=4f64823161a9b823b7bf8acb415a5008c562f1e917f5462e96c9a1d9bbbe217c" alt="Ace the Interview Workshop event flyer second page." class="wp-image-191" /></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:details -->
<details id="Ace-the-Interview" class="wp-block-details"><summary>Ace the Interview Workshop</summary><!-- wp:list {"ordered":true} -->
<ol class="wp-block-list"><!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>Resume &amp; Behavioral Interview Process</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>Technical Interviews &amp; Technical Process Ideation</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>
<!-- /wp:list --></details>
<!-- /wp:details -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"style":{"color":{"text":"#011d49"},"elements":{"link":{"color":{"text":"#011d49"}}}}} -->
<p class="has-text-color has-link-color" style="color:#011d49">The CIS Dept. of Brooklyn College Presents:<br>2-Part Technical Workshop Series<br>ACE THE INTERVIEW<br>with John Cline, Founder and CTO of ShelfLife and Emilie Hsieh, Founder and CEO, Allie</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list {"ordered":true,"style":{"color":{"text":"#011d49"},"elements":{"link":{"color":{"text":"#011d49"}}}}} -->
<ol style="color:#011d49" class="wp-block-list has-text-color has-link-color"><!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>Resume &amp; Behavioral Interview Process<br>Learn how to best market yourself on your resume and during the behavioral interview!<br>i.Thursday, October 16th, 2025 | 12:30 PM to 2:00 PM<br>Location: Student Center - Bedford Room (2nd Fl)</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item -->

<!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>Technical Interviews &amp; Technical Process Ideation<br>Learn how applicable skills on how to successfully get through the technical interview and learn how to determine and approach technical projects you want to work on!<br>i. Tuesday, October 21st, 2025 | 12:30 PM to 2:00 PM<br>Location: Student Center - Bedford Room (2nd Fl)</li>
<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:group {"style":{"color":{"text":"#011d49"},"elements":{"link":{"color":{"text":"#011d49"}}}},"layout":{"type":"constrained"}} -->
<div class="wp-block-group has-text-color has-link-color" style="color:#011d49"><!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Attend both sessions to get the most from the experience!!</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Our Speakers:</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>John Cline<br>John Cline is the co-founder and CTO of ShelfLife. Prior to joining ShelfLife in 202, he led engineering teams at various companies in NYC including Google, Blue Apron, and eBay. Before joining tech, he worked in government for Homeland Security and served in the United States Air Force. John also created a mentorship program with Mouse.org for CUNY students to help prepare them for their first internships and jobs in tech.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Emilie Hsieh<br>Emilie Hsieh is the founder and CEO of Allie, a digital coach that helps companies measure and improve diversity and inclusion. She started her career as a management consultant to Fortune 500 companies where she saw firsthand the impact of team dynamics and working styles on culture, inclusion and belonging. Emilie helped launch a career prep and mentorship program for Computer Science students at Mouse.org and holds a BSE from Northwestern University.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>To register:<br>Scan the QR code or go to the following link:<br>https://tinyurl.com/ACEInterviewF25<br>Questions? Email 2xtechteam@gmail.com</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>
<!-- /wp:group -->]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[The CIS Dept. of Brooklyn College Presents:
2-Part Technical Workshop Series
ACE THE INTERVIEW
with John Cline, Founder and CTO of ShelfLife and Emilie Hsieh, Founder and CEO, Allie

1. Resume &amp; Behavioral Interview Process
Learn how to best market yourself on your resume and during the behavioral interview!
i.Thursday, October 16th, 2025 | 12:30 PM to 2:00 PM
Location: Student Center - Bedford Room (2nd Fl)

2. Technical Interviews &amp; Technical Process Ideation
Learn how applicable skills on how to successfully get through the technical interview and learn how to determine and approach technical projects you want to work on!
i. Tuesday, October 21st, 2025 | 12:30 PM to 2:00 PM
Location: Student Center - Bedford Room (2nd Fl)

Attend both sessions to get the most from the experience!!]]></excerpt:encoded>
		<wp:post_id>185</wp:post_id>
